{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-14T06:22:38.510Z","evidence":{"commit":"9312151ff22dc79a3e977e98c4dd08167c30d4f1"},"content":"Scenario 18 (warren-82ea) is the only acceptance scenario that boots its own warren+burrow topology inside run(). It calls bootInProcMulti (scripts/acceptance/lib/inproc.ts) to spawn N burrows with auth-on (no --no-auth, BURROW_API_TOKEN per worker) plus warren via WARREN_CONFIG_FILE pointing at a generated warren.toml with [[workers]] rows. Distinct from bootInProc to keep the single-burrow scenarios 01-17 untouched.","id":"mx-d9123a"}
{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-14T06:22:43.649Z","evidence":{"commit":"9312151ff22dc79a3e977e98c4dd08167c30d4f1"},"content":"stub-shell agent in the acceptance harness (scripts/acceptance/lib/stub-agent/agent.sh) emits raw-text stdout; burrow's raw-text parser never produces a state_change with type=result|agent_end, so warren's detectRuntimeTerminal (src/runs/stream.ts) never fires and the run row stays 'running' forever. Scenarios that need a naturally-terminating run must use the 'pi' agent (which emits agent_end via pi-stub-agent.sh) or explicitly POST /runs/:id/cancel. Scenario 18 uses 'pi' for runs whose succeeded state matters (affinity warm-up, post-drain failover) and 'stub-shell' with [sleep_ms=8000] + cancel for runs that must stay in-flight.","id":"mx-8497a7"}
{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-14T06:22:50.089Z","evidence":{"commit":"9312151ff22dc79a3e977e98c4dd08167c30d4f1"},"content":"Two-project fixtures (scenario 18): warren.fixtures.ts only builds one sample project. To get a second project from the same fixture (needed for affinity-vs-other-project assertions), the scenario appends a second [url \"<sampleProjectPath>\"] / insteadOf rewrite to a per-scenario git-config file before bootInProcMulti, then POST /projects with a distinct fake gitUrl (e.g. https://github.com/warren-acceptance/sample-b.git). warren keys projects by gitUrl so the two URLs yield independent project rows backed by the same on-disk source repo.","id":"mx-194a67"}
{"type":"pattern","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-14T16:06:49.874Z","evidence":{"commit":"aa4900ec48d272def2ff0a0fd82ac48c63da5c09"},"name":"ScenarioSkipped: env-gated scenario skip protocol","description":"Acceptance scenarios can throw ScenarioSkipped (or call skipScenario(reason)) from scripts/acceptance/lib/assert.ts when a precondition isn't met (e.g. scenario 19 / warren-on-postgres requires WARREN_TEST_PG_URL). runScenarios catches it and records the scenario with status='skipped' + error=<reason>; the harness exit code stays 0 (skip is not failure). Used by scenario 19 so the default 'bun run scripts/acceptance/run.ts' invocation stays green on a stock dev box while CI matrix jobs that opt in light up the gated scenario. Distinct from the mode='in-proc' / mode='container' skip mechanism — that's per-scenario static metadata, ScenarioSkipped is per-invocation runtime detection. Future env-gated scenarios (real-LLM scenarios behind --real today) should adopt the same shape rather than throwing AcceptanceError.","files":[".seeds/issues.jsonl",".seeds/plans.jsonl","ROADMAP.md","SPEC.md","scripts/acceptance/lib/assert.ts","scripts/acceptance/lib/inproc.ts","scripts/acceptance/run.ts"],"id":"mx-5e2d2e"}
{"type":"decision","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-14T16:07:03.276Z","evidence":{"commit":"aa4900ec48d272def2ff0a0fd82ac48c63da5c09"},"title":"Per-scenario fresh CREATE DATABASE (not search_path schema) for scenario 19 pg isolation","rationale":"Two isolation shapes were on the table for scripts/acceptance/scenarios/19-warren-on-postgres.ts. (1) Per-scenario schema + search_path option, mirroring withDb() in src/db/testing.ts (mx-73932c). (2) Per-scenario CREATE DATABASE on a maintenance connection. Picked option 2.\n\nWhy not search_path schema: withDb() works because the test process opens drizzle itself and threads migrationsSchema through migratePg, so drizzle's __drizzle_migrations bookkeeping lives inside the per-test schema and is reaped by DROP SCHEMA CASCADE. Scenario 19 spawns warren as a subprocess via bootInProc; warren's openDatabase (src/db/client.ts) does NOT thread migrationsSchema (production doesn't need it). If scenario 19 isolated by search_path only, drizzle would write its journal to the default 'drizzle' schema and skip migrations on the next scenario run (journal hashes match) — yielding empty per-scenario schemas and broken warren boot. Widening warren's openDatabase surface for a test concern is also a smell.\n\nWhy CREATE DATABASE: a brand-new database has its own pristine drizzle schema. Warren's migrations run cleanly; bookkeeping lives in the per-scenario DB and is reaped along with it. Teardown uses DROP DATABASE IF EXISTS … WITH (FORCE) (pg ≥13) to evict any lingering pool clients from warren's pg.Pool that didn't disconnect on handle.stop().\n\nTrade-off: the WARREN_TEST_PG_URL role must hold CREATEDB privilege. That's stricter than CREATE SCHEMA, but in practice CI matrix jobs run pg as the superuser via docker-compose and dev operators dedicate a pg instance to acceptance — both meet CREATEDB. Documented in the scenario header and on the skip message.","id":"mx-70a89c"}
{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-14T16:07:06.810Z","evidence":{"commit":"aa4900ec48d272def2ff0a0fd82ac48c63da5c09"},"content":"bootInProc.dbUrl override (R-13 / warren-480a) accepts any sqlite-or-pg URL and writes only WARREN_DB_URL into the spawned warren's env (omitting the default WARREN_DB_PATH). Scenarios that need a per-test pg backend pass { dbUrl: 'postgres://...?options=...' } and skip the default '$tmpRoot/data/warren.db' sqlite path. Used by scripts/acceptance/scenarios/19-warren-on-postgres.ts; the loader's path↔url conflict warning (warren-e2ea) doesn't fire because WARREN_DB_PATH is not exported alongside.","id":"mx-8fe425"}
{"type":"failure","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-14T16:07:15.918Z","evidence":{"seeds":"warren-0f34","commit":"aa4900ec48d272def2ff0a0fd82ac48c63da5c09"},"description":"The repo layer is still sqlite-only (mx-994fa5: every repo uses bun-sqlite's synchronous .run() / .get() / .all()), and src/server/main.ts:336-344 (createReposForDialect) explicitly throws when db.dialect !== 'sqlite'. Plan pl-f17e bundled the pg widening implicitly into step 7 (warren-480a, this seed), but warren-480a's seed title is just the acceptance scenario — the repo widening is a much larger refactor that was never broken out as its own step. Result: scenario 19 lands as a skip-gated harness contract; flipping the gate to actually run end-to-end on pg is blocked.","resolution":"Wrote the scenario + harness machinery (SkipScenarioError, bootInProc.dbUrl wiring already in place from prior step). Filed warren-0f34 for the widening + gate lift. Scenario 19 flips from skipped → passed when warren-0f34 lands and WARREN_TEST_PG_URL is set.","id":"mx-80e365"}
{"type":"pattern","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-14T19:33:45.558Z","evidence":{"commit":"e76e0a8986b50173690e8e2e7798755bd9a53c02"},"name":"preview-scenario-own-stack-per-variant","description":"Acceptance scenario 20 boots a separate warren+burrow stack per variant (A=happy path, B=idle-TTL eviction) so each variant can pin its own WARREN_PREVIEW_HOST / WARREN_PREVIEW_IDLE_TTL / WARREN_PREVIEW_EVICTION_TICK_MS at boot — env knobs the harness-shared stack can't expose mid-run. Mirrors scenario 19's own-stack pattern (warren-480a) and uses bootInProc with a per-variant tmpRoot under \\`os.mkdtemp\\`. Each variant builds its own preview-enabled source repo (cp'd from ctx.fixtures.sampleProjectPath + augmented with .warren/defaults.json) under a unique fake git URL plus an augmented git-config that extends the outer harness redirects, keeping the shared fixture untouched and other scenarios unaffected.","files":[".seeds/issues.jsonl","Dockerfile","bun.lock","package.json","scripts/acceptance/run.ts"],"id":"mx-41ac58"}
{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-14T19:33:49.491Z","evidence":{"commit":"e76e0a8986b50173690e8e2e7798755bd9a53c02"},"content":"Preview acceptance scenarios skip on darwin via ScenarioSkipped(mx-1d31f0 message) because burrow's inbound-port-forwarding is Linux-only (bwrap netns + nsenter+nc relay in node_modules/@os-eco/burrow-cli/src/provider/local/inbound-forward.ts). Seatbelt doesn't isolate the netns on macOS, so the allocator's host port has nothing to forward to and the readiness probe times out. Skip is also gated on WARREN_TEST_DIALECT=postgres because the port allocator + eviction worker are SQLite-only today (src/server/main.ts:160-161, 253-254); pg path is the pl-f17e follow-up.","id":"mx-390bcf"}
{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-14T19:33:56.066Z","evidence":{"commit":"e76e0a8986b50173690e8e2e7798755bd9a53c02"},"content":"Variant B (idle-TTL eviction) in scenario 20 deliberately makes NO proxy requests after waiting for preview_state='live' so the idle clock falls back to preview_started_at instead of preview_last_hit_at — eviction fires deterministically WARREN_PREVIEW_IDLE_TTL ms after the launcher persists the live transition. A single proxy 200 would otherwise debounce-flush preview_last_hit_at (debounce 30s by default, src/preview/proxy.ts:67) and the eviction clock would reset, making the wait nondeterministic. Variant A flips this by setting WARREN_PREVIEW_IDLE_TTL=30m so its proxy 200/401 assertions don't race the worker.","id":"mx-192449"}
{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-14T19:34:00.265Z","evidence":{"commit":"e76e0a8986b50173690e8e2e7798755bd9a53c02"},"content":"Preview-enabled fixture build in scripts/acceptance/scenarios/20-preview.ts uses python3 -m http.server as preview.command for portability — universally on PATH across linux runners and inherited into the sandbox via PASSTHROUGH_ENV_KEYS=PATH (scripts/acceptance/lib/inproc.ts:467). The fixture commits a .warren/preview-www/index.html marker containing 'warren-preview-ok' so a proxy 200 with that body in the response proves end-to-end routing (host header parse → cookie verify → upstream forward → sidecar response) instead of accepting any 200. Marker is asserted with substring match via response.bodySnippet.includes('preview-ok').","id":"mx-87d34c"}
{"type":"failure","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-14T21:57:29.479Z","evidence":{"seeds":"warren-fe03","commit":"1369d6beb75da0083ea85e5b5fe308926be0fce7"},"description":"Skip-gated acceptance scenarios mask shipped bugs when CI doesn't set the gating env var. Scenario 19 (warren-on-postgres) skip-gates on WARREN_TEST_PG_URL via ScenarioSkipped — designed so 'bun run scripts/acceptance/run.ts' stays green on a stock machine. .github/workflows/ci.yml never sets WARREN_TEST_PG_URL and only runs 'bun test' (unit) — acceptance scenarios are run separately. Net: scenario 19 has never actually executed in CI, allowing the half-shipped R-13 (warren-2680) to merge unchecked. Lesson: skip-gated scenarios need explicit opt-in CI coverage, not just 'lights up when env is set' — without the matrix wire-up, the gate is silent.","resolution":"warren-fe03 plans the fix: add a postgres:16 service container to a CI matrix job, set WARREN_TEST_PG_URL on that job, run scenario 19 there. Folded into plan pl-f1be step 6. Going forward: any new skip-gated scenario should be paired with a CI matrix entry as part of the same PR — file an issue if you find a skip gate without a corresponding CI opt-in.","id":"mx-96eaab"}
{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-14T22:44:57.933Z","evidence":{"commit":"79f3a2b75a460f9b5a6df46692aeca6522d9da8b"},"content":"Scenario 19 (warren-on-postgres, warren-d4c6) verified green against real postgres:16 after R-13 adapter migration (pl-f1be steps 1-7). Three consecutive in-proc runs ~3.7-3.8s each with WARREN_TEST_PG_URL=postgres://warren:warren@127.0.0.1:54319/warren_test against an ephemeral docker postgres:16 container. The scenario CREATEs a per-run database (suffix warren_acc19_<hex>), boots warren+burrow there, validates /readyz db_reachable.message='dialect=postgres', spawns a stub run, kills warren mid-stream, restarts, and asserts events resume from MAX(burrow_event_seq)+1 with no seq gaps. Closes pl-f1be acceptance #3.","id":"mx-95127e"}
{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-15T02:59:18.295Z","evidence":{"seeds":"warren-7b3c","commit":"8460b5893e4fb8bf7277388eb05bc118fbf9535d"},"content":"Path-mode preview acceptance scenarios (scripts/acceptance/scenarios/20-preview-path.ts, warren-7b3c) boot warren with WARREN_PREVIEW_MODE=path and deliberately leave WARREN_PREVIEW_HOST unset — that's the zero-domain operator assertion the path-mode plan exists to make. Path-mode proxy preamble + login handler both wire up when only mode=path is set (no host required), per src/server/main.ts:286,331.","id":"mx-d54e6b"}
{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-15T02:59:22.128Z","evidence":{"seeds":"warren-7b3c","commit":"8460b5893e4fb8bf7277388eb05bc118fbf9535d"},"content":"Asserting the path-mode HTML <base> rewrite (warren-ab3a) from an acceptance scenario requires the upstream fixture to serve a real HTML document with a <head> tag — bare-text files served as text/html (e.g. scenario 20's 'warren-preview-ok\\n' index) skip injection because injectBaseHref returns null on documents with no parseable <head> within HTML_HEAD_LOOKAHEAD_BYTES. scripts/acceptance/scenarios/20-preview-path.ts (warren-7b3c) writes a real <html><head>…</head><body>…</body></html> document so the assertion lands.","id":"mx-789ebf"}
{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-15T03:39:20.379Z","evidence":{"seeds":"warren-87f9","commit":"12db131a190ee1fac93fef5745a3c9a108660051"},"content":"Scenario 21 (scripts/acceptance/scenarios/21-claude-code-cost-smoke.ts, warren-87f9) is the claude-code parallel of scenario 16's pi cost smoke. It dispatches POST /runs agent=claude-code against a stub runtime registered in burrow-with-stub.ts that OVERRIDES burrow's built-in claude-code runtime — burrow's AgentRegistry uses Map.set so client.agents.register(buildClaudeAcceptanceRuntime()) with id='claude-code' cleanly replaces the real-CLI-invoking built-in. Stub script tools/claude-code-stub-agent.sh emits stream-json with a fixed result envelope (cost 0.000421, 1200 input, 400 output, 5000 cache_read, 200 cache_create); scenario asserts all five run columns are non-null + positive after terminal.","id":"mx-06a64b"}
{"type":"failure","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-15T03:50:10.528Z","evidence":{"seeds":"warren-a82b","commit":"97b4cb64489150a45dd00853eb4eedba73af1c24"},"tags":["preview","acceptance","coverage-gap"],"relates_to":["mx-87d34c"],"description":"Preview acceptance scenarios (scripts/acceptance/scenarios/20-preview*.ts) exclusively use 'python3 -m http.server' as the sidecar (per mx-87d34c). The pi-compat node-shim symlink (Dockerfile:89) only manifests when the sidecar's dev command resolves through Node's bin shebangs — so python http server runs cleanly while every real Node JS framework (next/vite/remix) hits Bun's built-in module gaps. 2026-05-15 dogfood (warren-a82b) discovered this only because run_jegavdzfbrpc on jayminwest.com used 'pnpm dev'. CI was green throughout. The acceptance coverage shape (probe a port, not exercise the runtime) was the gap.","resolution":"Add a Node-runtime preview scenario alongside 20-preview*.ts that boots a minimal 'next dev' or 'vite dev' inside the burrow and asserts 2xx on /. Keep the python http scenario for the proxy/HTML-rewrite paths (it's faster). Run both on CI. Optionally: a scenario per package manager (npm/pnpm/bun) to catch installer-shape regressions.","id":"mx-4a73b4"}
{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-15T15:47:05.555Z","evidence":{"seeds":"warren-65ef","commit":"3c8ab3660abc085d6794d2022bef7e7b2e840cdc"},"relates_to":["mx-1a4c30"],"content":"Scenario 22 (scripts/acceptance/scenarios/22-seeds-extensions-roundtrip.ts, warren-65ef) is the manual-dispatch half of the R-01 seeds-extensions producer contract: POST /runs with seedId stamps {role,trigger:'manual',lastRunId,lastRunAt} onto the seed via sd update --extensions; a bogus seedId surfaces a seeds_extension_write_failed system event without rolling the run back. Scenario 15 covers the cron-tick half (trigger:'scheduled' + scheduledFor clear + lastScheduledRun). Both share the bootstrap-config.yaml-if-missing posture so they can run against the harness's shared sample project clone without contaminating sibling scenarios; both reset the source repo's .seeds/issues.jsonl at teardown for idempotent re-runs.","id":"mx-cc0d7b"}
{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-15T17:12:29.871Z","evidence":{"seeds":"warren-b2f9","commit":"476f497f536b323a66255af69c2ffad99b13eca2"},"content":"Scenario 23 (scripts/acceptance/scenarios/23-canopy-project-tier.ts, warren-b2f9) covers R-03 / pl-fef5 project-tier roundtrip end-to-end. Pattern: bootstrap project-tier .canopy/ in the sample-source repo via 'cn init' + 'cn create' + 'cn sync' (mirrors the canopy-source fixture's pattern), commit, then POST /projects/:id/refresh so the warren clone fetches it. Re-uses the existing stub-shell agent name at project tier so listing/spawn override behavior is observable against the library tier scenario 02 registers. Acceptance #7 of pl-fef5 originally called for slot 22, but 22 was claimed by seeds-extensions-roundtrip; scenario lands at 23.","id":"mx-966796"}
{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-17T20:07:11.500Z","evidence":{"seeds":"warren-0c8e","commit":"d734c5853c26c9829def22de34ba61963df1c611"},"relates_to":["mx-87d34c"],"content":"Scenario 24 (scripts/acceptance/scenarios/24-preview-node-runtime.ts, warren-0c8e) is the post-warren-a82b regression check for the bun-shim → real-Node Dockerfile change: preview command is 'node ./.warren/preview-server.js' and the script exits 1 when process.versions.bun is defined, so if /usr/local/bin/node ever gets re-symlinked at the bun-shim the readiness probe deadlines out. Skips if 'node' is not on host PATH (in-proc mode forwards host PATH into the sandbox via PASSTHROUGH_ENV_KEYS); deployed container always has Node 22 from NodeSource (Dockerfile:64-65). Mirrors scenario 20's subdomain-mode boot pattern + cookie-gated proxy GET; assertion is the body marker 'warren-preview-node-ok'.","id":"mx-a5f5a3"}
{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-17T23:03:22.667Z","evidence":{"seeds":"warren-4e06","commit":"aa94b05adec7f1e9ce2714b42037a3de42b2715a"},"relates_to":["mx-a5f5a3"],"content":"Scenario 25 (scripts/acceptance/scenarios/25-plot-roundtrip.ts, warren-4e06) is the Plot integration end-to-end roundtrip for pl-2047. Builds its own Plot-enabled fixture project under ctx.tmp/scenario-25-fixture (mirrors scenario 18's two-project pattern: appends an insteadOf line to the shared ctx.tmp/git-config so warren clones via the fake gitUrl). Asserts: (a) hasPlot=true after clone (warren-4e20), (b) host-side run_dispatched lands on the project's .plot/pl-<id>.events.jsonl post-spawn (warren-e848), (c) no-plot dispatch is byte-identical (no plot.* events, plotId null on every NDJSON envelope, no stub-agent PLOT_ID echo). Env-reaches-sandbox + sandbox plot append + reap-time mirror assertions are soft-skipped behind a logger.warn block — they depend on burrow-cli@0.3.1 parsing body.env (filed warren-a346).","id":"mx-af2627"}
{"type":"pattern","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-17T23:03:30.665Z","evidence":{"seeds":"warren-a346","commit":"aa94b05adec7f1e9ce2714b42037a3de42b2715a"},"name":"acceptance-soft-skip-upstream-blocked","description":"Soft-skip pattern for upstream-dependency-blocked assertions: when an end-to-end acceptance assertion is blocked on a known upstream gap (e.g. warren-a346 — burrow's POST /burrows doesn't yet parse body.env so warren-e26f's PLOT_ID/PLOT_ACTOR don't reach the sandbox), guard the dependent assertions with an 'envReached'-style precondition check that demotes them to ctx.logger.warn rather than throw. Tag both the JSDoc header and the in-body comment with a SOFT_SKIP_REASON marker pointing to the follow-up seed id, and structure the conditional so that when the upstream lands the assertions auto-promote to hard requirements (no rewrite needed). Scenario 25 (warren-4e06) is the prototype.","files":[".mulch/expertise/acceptance.jsonl",".seeds/issues.jsonl","scripts/acceptance/lib/stub-agent/agent.sh","scripts/acceptance/run.ts"],"id":"mx-384467"}
{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-18T01:37:39.813Z","evidence":{"seeds":"warren-ae00","commit":"77552c9a66ff3284c0204229d2f8b684fcb2320f"},"content":"Scenario 26 (scripts/acceptance/scenarios/26-plan-run-roundtrip.ts, warren-ae00) is the plan-run roundtrip. Three children dispatched serially via the coordinator against an in-proc warren+burrow stack. Uses agent=claude-code (NOT stub-shell — raw-text outputFormat never emits a runtime-terminal envelope so detectRuntimeTerminal never fires, leaving warren runs stuck in 'running' forever; that's why scenarios 04/09/10 cancel mid-run). WARREN_GH_FETCH_OVERRIDE=merged short-circuits GH REST calls inside src/runs/pr.ts (openPullRequest + checkPullRequestMerged) and loadAutoOpenPrConfigFromEnv synthesizes a stub token so reap's empty-token gate doesn't skip pr_open. WARREN_STUB_NO_COMMIT_SEEDS is a comma-list (forwarded via burrow.toml [env].optional in fixtures.ts) of seed ids whose closeseed dispatch produces no commits — drives the coordinator's trivial-merge branch (commitsAhead=0 + reap.empty_push → child merged without GH polling).","id":"mx-8e77bd"}
{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-18T04:47:04.628Z","evidence":{"seeds":"warren-97a3","commit":"662e32b88c98b00fc68c9383201c061f00a03071"},"relates_to":["mx-8e77bd"],"content":"Scenario 27 (scripts/acceptance/scenarios/27-plan-run-plot-roundtrip.ts, warren-97a3 / pl-7937 step 8) is the PlanRun + Plot composition roundtrip — boots a per-scenario warren stack (in-proc only, mirrors scenario 26) against a fixture committing both .seeds/ (two plans, four seeds — pl-acc-27-plot has SEED_A/B/C with SEED_C in WARREN_STUB_NO_COMMIT_SEEDS for the trivial-merge branch; pl-acc-27-base has SEED_D for the no-plot baseline) and .plot/ (one Plot pre-transitioned drafting → ready → active by the fixture so the auto-done has an active plot to terminate). Asserts the full warren-c900/b89f/b290 surface end-to-end: plan_run.plotId echoed in POST response, plan_run_dispatched landed on the Plot, three children all merged with run.plotId set, per-child run_dispatched accumulated for every child including the trivial-merge, plot.json status flipped to 'done', status_changed → done event by user:operator landed, and plan_run.plot_auto_done on the plan-run event stream. SOFT_SKIP for the per-child PLOT_ID/PLOT_ACTOR sandbox env (warren-a346, shared with scenario 25). Byte-identical baseline: a SECOND POST without plot_id (using pl-acc-27-base/SEED_D so children remain open) returns plotId=null and emits zero new Plot events for its own IDs.","id":"mx-15e4da"}
{"type":"failure","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-18T04:47:12.443Z","evidence":{"seeds":"warren-6f25","commit":"662e32b88c98b00fc68c9383201c061f00a03071"},"description":"Naive 'read .plot/<id>.events.jsonl once after plan completes' assertions miss per-child run_dispatched and the host-side plan_run_dispatched event — refreshProject (src/projects/refresh.ts:139, git reset --hard origin/<ref>) fires before each spawnRun and discards uncommitted appender writes between children, so the on-disk events.jsonl after plan-success only contains the LAST surviving writes (the final child's run_dispatched + the auto-done status_changed). Similarly, plot.json status='done' reverts to 'active' after any post-auto-done refresh.","resolution":"Tail the events.jsonl every ~100ms throughout plan execution with a setInterval poller that accumulates unique lines into a Set, started BEFORE the POST so plan_run_dispatched is captured even if the coordinator's first tick races the first poll. After waitForPlanState succeeds, wait ~1.5s (POST_PLAN_TAIL_FLUSH_MS) and tickOnce() once more so the auto-done's status_changed lands in the Set before parsing. See startPlotEventsTail() in scripts/acceptance/scenarios/27-plan-run-plot-roundtrip.ts. Underlying production issue tracked at warren-6f25.","id":"mx-736365"}
{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-18T04:47:17.039Z","evidence":{"seeds":"warren-97a3","commit":"662e32b88c98b00fc68c9383201c061f00a03071"},"relates_to":["mx-af2627"],"content":"scripts/acceptance/lib/stub-agent/claude-code-agent.sh emits a 'claude-stub: PLOT_ID=<id> PLOT_ACTOR=<actor>' text assistant envelope (jsonl-claude format) when PLOT_ID is present in env — added for scenario 27 (warren-97a3) to give the per-child PLOT_ID/PLOT_ACTOR sandbox-injection assertion an agent-side hook. Gated on PLOT_ID so plan-run scenarios that don't bind a Plot (26, 17) are unaffected. Mirrors the existing PLOT_ID echo on stub-shell agent.sh (warren-4e06). Currently soft-skipped pending warren-a346 (burrow doesn't forward body.env into the sandbox).","id":"mx-deeeac"}
